content:
Use date functions to adjust or calculate values from dates. For example, you can add time, find time until, and extract a day of the week from date fields. The arguments for date functions are date fields.

When entering a formula, use the API name of the field in the expression, not the label. The parameters section is surrounded by parentheses. 

add_months startDate is the date field calculated on. num_months is the number of months added to the startDate.

current_date Returns the current date. 
current_timestamp Returns the current date and time.
datediff endDate is the later of the two dates you are finding the difference between. startDate is the earlier of the two dates you are finding the difference between.
date_add startDate is the date field calculated on. num_days is the number of days added to the startDate.

date_format field is a date field/timestamp or string to be converted to the given format. 'format' is the date and time format pattern to follow.
date_sub startDate is the date field calculated on. num_days is the number of days subtracted from the startDate.
day date is the date field to extract the day of month from.
dayofmonth date is the date field to extract the day of month from.
dayofweek date is the date field to extract the day of week from.
dayofyear date is the date field to extract the day of year from.

months_between timestamp2 is one of the timestamps to compare. timestamp1 is the other timestamp to compare.
now Returns the current date and time in the specified format.
to_date field is a date string field that you want to convert. 'format' is the date and time format pattern to follow.
to_timestamp field is a timestamp string field that you want to convert. 'format' is the timestamp format pattern to follow.
to_unix_timestamp timestamp is a date/timestamp or string which is returned as a UNIX timestamp. format is the date/time format pattern to follow.
trunc field is a timestamp field. 'format' specifies the part of the timestamp to truncate.

These functions are relative to when the batch data transform runs. All date and datetime functions are based on the UTC time zone. When Custom Time Zone Support is enabled, date functions and DateTime functions are separated.
title: Date Functions for Formulas in Salesforce Data Cloud
